Risk Reward for ORIX JREIT (8954. T) has been updated
We account for the 2- to- 1 stock split on September 1, 2025. We also fine- tune our DPS estimates and our price target. Our valuation remains unchanged.
MORGAN STANLEY MUFG SECURITIES CO., LTD.

Elevated DPS to continue as further sales gains are booked ahead
Key: Historical Stock Performance Current Stock Price Price Target
Source: Refinitiv, Morgan Stanley Research
In Feb 2025, announced first property transactions with sponsor group in 5 1/2 years. We expect increased sponsor support, including property transactions.

Expect these transactions to maintain DPS growth of \(3\%\) or more from base of ¥1,910. with potential upside if further property sales are booked and proceeds distributed. We expect gains from already announced property sales to be booked from FT8/26 as well, and even if property is not sold, it is possible to use internal reserves. We expect improved portfolio profitability through replacement of properties.
Source: Refinitiv, Morgan Stanley Research
Self- help: Positive View descriptions of Risk Rewards Themes here
DPS is unchanged from the base case.
Target dividend yield is calculated assuming the 10- year JGB yield (used as the risk- free rate) declines 40bps.
Fair value is based on 12- month DPS estimate of ¥4,730 and a target dividend yield of \(3.9\%\) .
Large tenant departures result in a lower portfolio occupancy rate, and lower DPS, than we envisage.
Target dividend yield is calculated assuming the 10- year JGB yield (used as the risk- free rate) declines 40bps.
Fair value is based on a 12- month DPS estimate of ¥3,910 and a \(4.7\%\) dividend yield.
- 3%+ annual DPS growth from a starting point of ¥1,910- Better portfolio profitability and recording of sales gains due to property reshuffling
